cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on inter-domain Traffic Engineering and RTT measurements. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possible category as the paper mentions the detection of path changes due to routing protocols and load balancing, which can have security implications. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper proposes a data transformation to improve the detection performance of existing methods. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper analyzes the correlation between RTT and path changes. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a less likely category but possible as the paper proposes a scoring method specifically tailored for RTT measurements.
